entries.text: The rough diamond of a star who appeared like a comet...
I just did a chatting stream recently.
I kinda want to play a game.
But starting a long RPG is a bit...
I want to do a long game, but...
I can't stream overly frequently right now.
The Live is getting close, too.
What's something that doesn't use my throat?
I want to do a grindy task game.
Nothing is really trending right now.
Hmm, maybe I'll play something from the past?
What ever happened to Fast Food Simulator?
I did the solo op thing way too much.
I just remembered the past, but...
Back when this Fast Food Simulator was trending,
The Holo-mems were all playing it together.
But my schedule was bad, so I could never join.
And as a result of mastering it alone...
I became a human incapable of cooperating with others.
I'm pretty sure that's the past I have with this game.
From there, I turned into a solo-op player.
People did play with me behind the scenes,
They tried to split roles like, "You do this, you do that,"
But because I had become a sad solo-op machine,
Well, I just played a little bit to test it out,
I was trying to remember what it was like.
I'll set the game difficulty to Easy for now,
Just let me play on Easy.
And I remembered a bit just now,
So I think I'm good to go.
I need to froth the milk.
Just in case, I'll put another milk here...
I left it open after restocking.
Why are you only using one hand?!
I'll fry the chicken patties first.
Uh, I need to pour new oil.
I've never worked a part-time job.
I've got this area perfectly down.
So, um, fill from L. Right is L, middle M, left S.
I... I fried it in contaminated oil.
Eh, does that mean it's no good?
Eh, does that mean I'll get scolded?
I thought it was still okay.
I don't think it's that much.
Since the Live is coming up,
They didn't put much work in my schedule.
I feel like I can still go... wait.
I know, for things like this...
You just watch over it for a sec.
I feel like I can do it.
I feel like this contamination level is barely passable.
Let's push the limit. The limit.
It's okay, I can still go, still go.
Which one? Which is first? Which is first?
This year is more... than usual...
I don't know why it turned out like this, but...
"Is that thing you always say true?"
Maybe it's a problem of scale.
Should I just cook them all?
Actually, if it's just one more, let's cook it.
"Can you relax a bit after the Fes Live is over?"
This year, there is no future where I can relax.
Was there a flipping motion like this before?
And I put cheese on these ones.
I'm going to make this year a super busy year.
Pull it out, pull it out, pull it out first!
Whatever happens to that one slice, I don't care anymore!
Can I finally open the store?
Looking at these burgers makes me hungry.
Makes me want to eat one.
Which burger do you like? Cheese, right?
But I tried the Ebi Filet-O once and it was delicious.
Strawberry ice cream and Small Fries.
"Su-chan, did you try the Takenoko no Sato and Kinoko no Yama McFlurry?"
"Did you eat Spichiki?" I haven't eaten Spichiki.
Fried Potato and Strawberry Ice Cream.
I thought I was just remembering how to play...
Coffee, Vanilla Ice Cream, Chicken Nuggets.
Crap, the Chicken Nuggets aren't ready.
Hamburger, should I do this one first?
Don't get mad over ice amount!
Wait, I'm running out of patties.
Do I not need to fry this much?
How many times did I place it?
Um, cola is in the back.
Not making any is also bad.
Chicken is always left over like this.
Maybe just one pack is enough.
Why is there so much left?
Need to put this milk away.
Actually, not really enough over here either.
Maybe one pack of these is fine.
I like it when it's not too sweet.
It makes me happy when it's not overly sweet.
Easy mode was way too easy so...
Do I go to the main menu?
I don't really like tea itself that much.
I'll stick to one of these.
Frying nuggets too! They take time, so pre-cooking is best.
Crap, forgot to put the cheese away! I knew I'd forget!
Pull it up. Now it's open.
Eh, is that enough nuggets? Really?
Just this much chicken is fine.
Did I run out of meat?
Let's just grill all of these.
Um, uh, cheese, cheese, cheese, cheese.
Chee, chee, chee, chee, chi, chee, chee, chi, chee, chee, chee, cheese falls.
I'll put this cheese away now.
Because I always forget to put it away.
Actually, I like Sukiya's Cheese Gyudon.
It started being used as a derogatory term.
I've been mad about this forever.
Don't use "Sukiya's Cheese Gyudon" as a slur!
Having nothing to do in the meantime is a bit...
Is it easier if I fill them?
Crap, I didn't put milk in.
Ah, ui, ui, ui, what is this guy?
Let's just have this guy leave.

This is... chicken, so... this guy is going home. Chicken. This is Pop-san? What's this Pop-san? Pop-san don't you need this? Um, um, Noma-berry? One of them. Strawberry. OK. Um, anyone need ice cream? You. Oi.
Um, starting with the easy ones. Milky Coffee.
Eh? Milky Coffee and... Water and Fried Potato L.
Ah, I have it. I have it.
The other one is probably here.
Wait, didn't I make the burger?
Wait, maybe it wasn't that guy?
I want a trash can nearby.
"How many people is this game originally for?"
I've only ever played it alone on stream.
It's not that I'm being left out!
Well, this much leftover is probably just right.
Nuggets and fries are about right too.
There was a lot of stuff I didn't understand.
Let's just trash all this stuff.
Trash around here probably doesn't matter, so leave it.
Um, around here... Restock, restock. Hey, it's empty!
Mustard... Mustard doesn't go down much.
Mayo tends to run out. Um...
I have to throw this away.
Why is there no trash can nearby?
I want to increase trash cans.
In PlateUp, I can add more.
L looks a bit low, but is it okay?
I never bought anything before, but I was supposed to buy stuff like this?
Wait, gotta buy lots of stuff.
There's a chat time! Chat time!
See, there's a Just Chatting phase!
I was wondering when it would end...
I watched it with my sister.
Just the parts I was curious about.
Not really watching the whole thing thoroughly again.
Rei's PV was super meaningful too.
Shocking that that's a Netflix exclusive.
They play it in theaters too, I heard.
Like a limited one week run.
"Reading the novel makes it easier to understand."
"Eh, are you gonna play Poppy Playtime 5?"
I like how each chapter is bite-sized.
Eh, is the next one the last one?
Is it the last? Could it be?
If 5 comes, it wouldn't be weird if it's the end.
"What did Su-chan eat on Meat Day (Feb 29)?"
Uh, I don't really know, what was it...
"Not a cut of meat you eat at home."
I didn't eat it at home.
It's too fatty, I can't eat a lot.
The past Me stockpiled so much!
Must have been running the shop hard.
Hachinosu (Reticulum) is a bit greasy, but...
Marucho (Small Intestine) is good, but just "good".
While that's happening, get these ready...
I just had to do this!
These are roughly OK. Pour in milk...
Then this and fry the nuggets.
Potatoes, potatoes, potatoes, I want to eat potatoes~
Whenever we have a dinner party at my house...
Potatoes are almost guaranteed to be...
I want to run a potato specialty shop.
I went to a potato specialty shop once.
But it wasn't what I was looking for.
In Ginza or somewhere, there's a shop where you choose potato types.
I want to go there once.
Usually, it's just enjoying different sauces.
Frying while open is tough too...
Yeah, frying during the rush is hard so...
"Ibaraki has a fried potato specialty shop."
I eat soba, but not really "Wanko" style.
There are these crispy fries among frozen ones.
And this is Double Hamburger and Light Splash Cola.
Thought I should serve non-burger people first, but maybe not good.
And Fried Potato M and Water.
I don't have Fried Potato M.
3, 2, 1, 3, 3, um, One Burger, 3, 1, 2, um, 4, 4, 3, One Burger, um, 2, 3...
Going from the top! Splash Cola.
Cup, Potato S, Strawberry Ice Cream, L and Coffee.
There is coffee. Did I pour it?
L and Coffee. Is it in there? Really?
I don't know what's what anymore!
"This isn't the size of fried potato I ordered."
Isn't there a more efficient way?
Seems like it could be done more efficiently.
I'm totally relying on brain capacity...
Just barely managing within my brain's limit.
Want to optimize like in PlateUp.
I want them way too much!
Ah, but I still have to cook?
Ah, I want someone to cook.
An hour and a half passed in a blink.
Yoisho. Obviously. It's not like I was recruiting.
You guys got it wrong. Wrong. I'm just getting my hopes up on my own.
Just me getting excited for nothing. I'm such a fool.
Madomagi watchalong was funny. Everyone is busy before Fes.
Ah, totally empty. Restock. Let's restock and end for today.
"Eiko-chan's content is all funny." I know right.
Thank you. Chicken Nuggets. "Recruit part-timers next time?"
Let's make it popular again. This Food Simulator game. Again.
Eh, will it get popular? "It's old news." "You're the only one playing that." I feel like they'll say that.
"Still playing that?" Like playing the watermelon game alone forever.
What? Oh, it's full. First time full. So I place Trash Bags.
I fried them but it was enough. Want some?
Take them home. Don't have (bags)? Eat, eat.
You guys can go home too. Go home. Pour coffee...
Nice. Yup. Eat up. Didn't use much milk either.
Pickles and Lettuce and... gotta buy.
If I hire, will they come right now?
No, placing neatly might be my job?
I think I have Ice Cream Cups.
Changed chairs but they didn't change!
Gotta put stuff away from here.
They bring it in, but put it in the wrong spot.
My Type A personality will scream.
Hey, you know this is the spot!
Idiot, idiot, idiot! You crap! Scum!
I don't have to put it inside?
Guess this stuff doesn't need to be in.
"That rookie is on their first day..."
But do it right next time.
I hate saying the same thing twice.
Making it pleasant for tomorrow's Me.
Because I've been sleeping and waking early recently...
Tomorrow is a 6-day work week start.
So I'm trying to get used to waking up early now.
"Early? Well, for Su-chan, that is early."
And so, cleaning is done. Yup.
Nuggets too, potatoes too... gotta change soon.
Hmm, hmm. Oh, it looks like this.
A bit subtle though. This weird billiard-table-like desk.
Toilet. Thought toilet cleaning might be added.
So, played Fast Food Simulator today.
Game Over. How's this room now?
This room is a bit messy right now, but come in. Messy but come in.
Sorry, sorry, a bit messy. It's messy.
Well, cleaning it now, wait a sec.
"Waiting at the entrance." You're the kind type.
Thanks for waiting for the opening.
"Bought a Fan." Thanks. Eh, everyone, write big text on your Fans!
Ah, local sales notification is out?
What was I doing? Seriously. Too behind. Was a bit hectic.
"Shoot for the Moon is danceable." Thanks.
"Towel not arrived yet?" Saw people saying it arrived. Variance? Seriously thinking about making an info account.
Thinking I should make an information account. Su-chan has given up.
Did my goods come out? Not yet? Not yet? Out?
Yeah, I leave it to the Star-gazers.
Eh, as long as it fits regulations.
Like "No huge ones" or "No flashing ones", usual rules.
"Holo Shop jacked by Shoot for the Moon?" No event started.
Has a place to buy drinks.
Too much info, I don't know!
I signed so many autographs recently.
Signing while wondering "What is this for?"
"What is the thing for displaying at [Blank]?"
I'm probably the only Hololive talent...
Who gets worried about retiring at 60.
Gotta get throat and body ready for the 21st.
This week is almost over anyway.
Staying inside too much is bad so...
Go for a walk on off days.
Want to go to a puzzle game or play, but...
If I catch a cold, it's over.
It's over, so I'm worried. What to do?
Bad if I catch a cold. Flu is spreading.
We have something we've been warming up.
I think we'll be revealing it.
No, maybe no break this year.
Forgot to bring it up, so can't adjust schedule.
Usually the season for a long break though.
Gonna be hectic this year too.
Nope, haven't done it at all.
Gonna be busy around there too.
Thank you everyone for your hard work.
